==Abstract==

This IIP describes Pay to Script Hash (P2SH) for INTcoin, adapted from BIP 16 for ML-DSA-87 signatures.

==Motivation==

P2SH provides:
* Compact outputs (complex scripts represented by 20-byte hash)
* Sender simplicity (only need script hash, not full script)
* Fee efficiency (full script revealed only when spending)
* Privacy (spending conditions hidden until spent)

==Specification==

===Script Format===

A P2SH output has the scriptPubKey:
<pre>
OP_HASH160 <20-byte-script-hash> OP_EQUAL
</pre>

The script hash is computed as:
<pre>
Hash160(redeemScript) = SHA3-256(redeemScript)[0:20]
</pre>

'''Note:''' INTcoin uses SHA3-256 truncated to 20 bytes, not RIPEMD160(SHA256).

===Spending===

To spend a P2SH output, the scriptSig must contain:
<pre>
<data1> <data2> ... <dataN> <serialized-redeem-script>
</pre>

